data.name: Attack Surface Identification
data.desc: This test launches asset profiling to identify target machine’s OS type, open ports, active services as well as websites’ domain names/sub-domain names, encryption key, web framework and external URL/URI exposures

data.name: Website Penetration
data.desc: This test launches cyber attacks against target websites, web applications and all the related attack surfaces.  The attack targets include: self-developed or CMS based websites.

data.name: Intranet Penetration (IP + Default crawler)
data.desc: This scenario uses port scanning and default web crawler to profile targets’ attack surface exposures and utilizes various network attack techniques to discover vulnerabilities and exploit risks of the targets.If user needs to customize web crawler or want to use crawler+proxy mode to bypass website login, please select web related scenarios for the task.

data.name: Weak Credential Exploit
data.desc: This test launches cyber attacks based on the sensitive information collected via weak credentials or unauthorized access exploits. Attack targets include but not limited to various application logins, web logins, Redis, Elasticsearch, ActiveMQ, Database etc.

data.name: 3rd Party Framework Penetration Testing
data.desc: This test launches cyber attackes against common used 3rd party framework such as Struts 2, Spring, Fastjson, ThinkPHP and many others.

data.name: Ransomware Attack Simulation
data.desc: This test utilizes various techniques frequently used by APT groups to perform ransomware attacks such as server remote command execution (RCE) attack, windows remote desktop rotocol (RDP), brute-force attack and etc.

data.name: Intranet Ransomware Attack Simulation
data.desc: This test utilizes various techniques frequently used by APT groups to perform ransomware attacks such as windows remote desktop rotocol (RDP), windows remote command execution (RCE) attack, weak password brute-force attack and etc.

data.name: 3rd Party Scanning Result Validation
data.desc: This test allows RidgeBot user to upload a 3rd party vulnerability test report, then launch a full penetration task to validate its result

data.name: Endpoint Security
data.desc: RidgeBot Botlet simulates the behavior of malicious software or downloads malware signatures to validate the security controls of the target endpoints. A test result with higher block rate indicates better endpoint protection

data.name: Data Exfiltration
data.desc: RidgeBot Botlet simulates the unauthorized movement of data from your server. A test result with higher block rate indicates more attack methods of data theft can be detected and prevented

data.name: Active Directory Information Recon
data.desc: RidgeBot Botlet simulates an attacker to gather useful resources in Windows Active Directory for elevated privilege, persist, and plundering information. A test result with higher block rate indicates the Windows AD server gets better protection in place.
